cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new approach for machine learning that involves incorporating soft unification into neural networks to learn variables and lift examples into invariants. This approach is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the five most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
